getAgentDescriptions

IAgentDescription[] getAgentDescriptions()
Get all AgentDescriptions. There are two ways of describing an agent, the get-/setDescription-methods deal with a 'human-readable' description, the get-/setAgentDescription-methods on the other hand deal with the FIPA-agentdescription, which is more technical and used for registering and searching for agents at the directory facilitator for example.

Returns:
The AgentType's AgentDescriptionModels as an array.

addAgentDescription

void addAgentDescription(IAgentDescription description)
Add an AgentDescription for this AgentType. There are two ways of describing an agent, the get-/setDescription-methods deal with a 'human-readable' description, the get-/setAgentDescription-methods on the other hand deal with the FIPA-agentdescription, which is more technical and used for registering and searching for agents at the directory facilitator for example.

Parameters:
description - the AgentType's AgentDescriptionModel.
